<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[105969]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Lluís Homar is "Terra Baixa"]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Pau Miró and Lluís Homar have made a stage adaptation of this Guimerà classic, Terra baixa,  with all the parts played by a single actor and with music by Sílvia Pérez Cruz.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Teatre Lliure presents one of the longest-awaited premières of the year. Directed by Pau Miró, Lluís Homar plays the roles in Àngel Guimerà&#8217;s classics <i>Terra Baixa</i>, alone on stage.</p>
<p>He plays not just the part of the ingenuous Manelic, who leaves the <em>terra alta</em>, out of the most turbulent of human passions, but also that of Marta and even master Sebastià, in other words, both Little Red Riding Hood and the Wolf. Pau Miró focuses the universality of the Catalan classic on one actor, in a play with music by Sílvia Pérez Cruz.</p>
